.\" Man page for osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
.\" Written in classic troff/groff format
.TH OSU-TRACK-QEMU-AGENTS 1 "2026-04-23" "osu-track-qemu-agents 0.2.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
osu-track-qemu-agents \- report OpenStack VMs with QEMU guest agent status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.PP
.B osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
.RB [ \-f | \-\-format
.IR FMT ]
.RB [ \-a | \-\-all\-projects ]
.RB [ \-d | \-\-domain
.IR DOMAIN ]
.RB [ \-i | \-\-issues\-only ]
.RB [ \-q | \-\-quiet ]
.PP
.B osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
.RB \-p | \-\-project
.I PROJECT
.RB [ \-d | \-\-domain
.IR DOMAIN ]
.RB [ \-f | \-\-format
.IR FMT ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
reports OpenStack VMs with their QEMU guest agent configuration and
communication status. For each VM, it shows:
.IP 1. 3
.B Agent Bus:
Whether
.B hw_qemu_guest_agent
is enabled in the source image (the virtio-serial device for agent communication).
.IP 2. 3
.B Agent Responding:
Whether the agent is actually communicating with the hypervisor.
.PP
.B Detection Methods (CLI/API only, no database access):
.IP \(bu 2
.B Agent Bus:
Checks image properties via the OpenStack CLI. For boot-from-volume VMs,
checks volume_image_metadata.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Agent Responding:
Uses the Nova diagnostics API. Presence of detailed memory statistics
(memory-unused, memory-available) indicates the balloon driver and agent
are communicating.
.PP
.B Status Indicators:
.IP \(bu 2
.B "\[u2713]"
\(em Yes (bus configured / agent responding)
.IP \(bu 2
.B "\[u2717]"
\(em No (bus not configured / agent not responding)
.IP \(bu 2
.B "?"
\(em Couldn't determine (VM not running, image deleted, etc.)
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Scope Options
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all\-projects
Include VMs from all projects (requires OpenStack admin privileges).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-domain " " \fIDOMAIN\fR
Report all VMs in projects belonging to the specified domain.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-project " " \fIPROJECT\fR
Limit output to a single project, specified by name or ID.
Can be combined with
.B \-d
for cross-domain project lookup.
.SS Filter Options
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-issues\-only
Show only VMs with agent issues (bus not configured or agent not responding).
Useful for identifying VMs that need attention.
.TP
.BR \-\-filter\-responding " " \fIVALUE\fR
Filter VMs by agent responding status. Valid values:
.BR yes " (agent communicating), "
.BR no " (agent not responding), "
.BR undetermined " (couldn't determine)."
.SS Output Options
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-format " " \fIFMT\fR
Set output format. Valid values are
.BR table " (default), " csv ", and " json .
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Suppress progress indicators.
.SS Other Options
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display usage information and exit.
.SH OUTPUT COLUMNS
.TP
.B ID
Instance UUID.
.TP
.B Name
Instance name.
.TP
.B Project
Project name (only shown with
.BR \-\-all\-projects " or " \-\-domain ).
.TP
.B Status
Nova instance state (ACTIVE, SHUTOFF, ERROR, etc.).
.TP
.B Agent Bus
Whether hw_qemu_guest_agent is set in the source image: \fB\[u2713]\fR (yes), \fB\[u2717]\fR (no), \fB?\fR (couldn't determine).
.TP
.B Responding
Whether the agent is communicating: \fB\[u2713]\fR (yes), \fB\[u2717]\fR (no), \fB?\fR (couldn't determine).
.TP
.B Image/Volume
Source image name, or "vol:<image-name>" for boot-from-volume VMs.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful execution.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred (missing dependencies, authentication failure, invalid options).
.SH EXAMPLES
Report VMs in the current project:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh
.fi
.RE
.PP
Report all VMs across all projects:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh --all-projects
.fi
.RE
.PP
Report all VMs in a specific domain:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh -d my-domain
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show only VMs with agent issues:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh --issues-only --all-projects
.fi
.RE
.PP
CSV output for spreadsheet analysis:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh -f csv --all-projects > agents.csv
.fi
.RE
.PP
JSON output for scripting (filter VMs without responding agent):
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ osu-track-qemu-agents.sh -f json --all-projects | jq '.[] | select(.agent_responding == false)'
.fi
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The script requires:
.IP \(bu 2
Valid OpenStack credentials sourced (e.g.,
.BR "source ~/openrc.sh" ).
.SS Permissions
.IP \(bu 2
.B Default (own project):
Regular OpenStack user.
.IP \(bu 2
.B --all-projects or -p <other-project>:
OpenStack admin.
.IP \(bu 2
.B --domain:
OpenStack admin or domain admin.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/openrc.sh
OpenStack credentials file (typical location).
.SH NOTES
.SS Why Check Both Bus and Responding?
.IP \(bu 2
.B Bus configured but not responding:
The image has hw_qemu_guest_agent=yes, but the agent is not installed,
not running, or the VM is powered off. For running VMs, this indicates
the qemu-guest-agent package needs to be installed.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Bus not configured but responding:
Unusual \(em the agent shouldn't be able to communicate without the virtio-serial
device. May indicate image metadata is incorrect.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Neither configured nor responding:
The VM was not created with agent support. Live migration features like
guest filesystem freeze will not work.
.SS Detection Limitations
.IP \(bu 2
Agent response detection only works for ACTIVE VMs.
.IP \(bu 2
The diagnostics API check relies on memory statistics from the balloon driver,
which typically accompanies the guest agent.
.IP \(bu 2
Boot-from-volume VMs inherit agent configuration from volume_image_metadata.
